Anonymous Sat 24 Dec 2022 17:08:02 No.53241357 Report

>>53239864
If anything, oil tends to be a lot cleaner than coal, if we're talking strictly about emissions. Extraction of oil is less energy-intensive, as a rule, too--drilling a well vs. digging very deep holes into the ground and hollowing it out from the inside, trying carefully to keep it from collapsing on the workers while doing it. That's one of the two big reasons petroleum supplanted coal so quickly as an energy source in industrialized nations. The other is the internal combustion engine, which is difficult to make work with coal. Not impossible--see also, Fischer-Tropsch Process--but the Fischer-Tropsch Process is itself wasteful and energy-intensive, requiring enormously expensive infrastructure to do on any significant scale.
